    "walkthroughs": [
      {
        "id": "snapback.welcome",
        "title": "Get Started with SnapBack",
        "description": "Learn the three protection levels and protect your first file in 2 minutes",
        "steps": [
          {
            "id": "snapback.understand-levels",
            "title": "Three Levels of Protection",
            "description": "SnapBack gives you precise control with three protection levels:\n\n**🟢 Watch** - Silent auto-snapshotting (no interruptions)\n\n**🟡 Warn** - Confirm before saving (safety prompt)\n\n**🔴 Block** - Required snapshot note (maximum protection)\n\nChoose the right level for each file based on how critical it is.",
            "media": {
              "markdown": "## When to Use Each Level\n\n### 🟢 Watch - Most Files\n- Configs you edit often\n- Code you're actively working on\n- Files where you want automatic safety\n\n### 🟡 Warn - Important Files\n- Files that affect multiple systems\n- Database migrations\n- Build configurations\n\n### 🔴 Block - Critical Files\n- `package.json`, `.env` files\n- Authentication code\n- Payment processing\n- Anything that could break production"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "snapback.protect-first-file",
            "title": "Protect Your First File",
            "description": "Let's protect a file together:\n\n1. Right-click any file in the Explorer\n2. Hover over **SnapBack: Set Protection Level**\n3. Choose **🧢 Watch Level** (silent mode)\n4. The file now gets automatic snapshots when you save\n\n[Open a file to try it now](command:workbench.action.quickOpen)",
            "media": {
              "markdown": "## Protection Levels Menu\n\nWhen you right-click a file, you'll see:\n\n``````\n\n**Pro Tip:** You can also use the Command Palette:\n- Press `Ctrl+Shift+P` (or `Cmd+Shift+P` on Mac)\n- Type \"SnapBack: Protect File\"\n- Choose your protection level"
            },
            "completionEvents": [
              "onCommand:snapback.protectFile",
              "onCommand:snapback.setWatchLevel"
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "snapback.see-it-work",
            "title": "See Protection in Action",
            "description": "Now make a change to your protected file and save it.\n\n✅ **Watch level** creates a snapshot silently\n✅ Status bar shows confirmation briefly\n✅ No interruptions to your flow\n\nNotice how the file badge in the Explorer shows it's protected.",
            "media": {
              "markdown": "## What Happens When You Save?\n\n### 🟢 Watch Level\n- Snapshot created automatically\n- Brief status bar message\n- No interruption\n\n### 🟡 Warn Level\n- Confirmation dialog appears\n- You can add a note (optional)\n- Click \"Save\" to continue\n\n### 🔴 Block Level\n- Dialog requires a note\n- Note helps you remember why you made the change\n- Cannot save without adding context"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "snapback.explore-snapshots",
            "title": "Snap Back (Restore Snapshots)",
            "description": "Open the SnapBack sidebar to see all your snapshots:\n\n1. Click the SnapBack icon in the Activity Bar (left sidebar)\n2. Browse your snapshot history\n3. Click any snapshot to view details\n4. Use \"Snap Back\" to restore\n\n[Open SnapBack View](command:workbench.view.extension.snapback)",
            "media": {
              "code": "## Viewing Your Snapshots\n\n### SnapBack Sidebar\nClick the SnapBack icon (🧢) in the Activity Bar to see:\n- All your snapshots in chronological order\n- File-specific snapshot history\n- Protected files list\n- Quick restore and compare actions\n\n### Protected Files View\nIn the Explorer sidebar, expand **SNAPBACK PROTECTED FILES** to:\n- See all protected files at a glance\n- View protection levels (🟢 Watch, 🟡 Warn, 🔴 Block)\n- Right-click for quick actions\n\n### Keyboard Shortcuts\n- `Ctrl+Alt+S` / `Cmd+Alt+S` - Create Snapshot\n- `Ctrl+Alt+Z` / `Cmd+Alt+Z` - Snap Back (Restore)\n- `Ctrl+Alt+P` / `Cmd+Alt+P` - Protect Current File\n\n💡 **Pro Tip:** Right-click any protected file for quick snapshot actions!"
            },
            "completionEvents": [
              "onView:snapback.main"
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "snapback.team-protection",
            "title": "Bonus: Team Protection Policies",
            "description": "Share protection policies with your team using `.snapbackrc` configuration:\n\n1. Create `.snapbackrc` in your repo root\n2. Add patterns with protection levels\n3. Commit to Git\n\n**Everyone on your team gets the same protection automatically.**",
            "media": {
              "code": "## Team Configuration Example\n\nCreate `.snapbackrc` in your project root:\n\n``````\n\n**Benefits:**\n- Consistent protection across the team\n- New team members get protection automatically\n- Reduce accidental breaking changes"
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "viewsWelcome": [
      {
        "view": "snapback.protectedFiles",
        "contents": "No protected files yet.\n\nProtect your first file to see it here.\n\n[🧢 Protect File](command:snapback.protectFile)\n\nLearn about [protection levels](command:snapback.openWalkthrough).",
        "when": "!snapback.hasProtectedFiles"
      }
    ],
    "jsonValidation": [
      {
        "fileMatch": ".snapbackrc",
        "url": "./schemas/snapbackrc.schema.json"
      }
    ]
  },
